description:
&lt;p&gt;18 Week Support are currently seekingaEndoscopy Band 8c Head of Nursing to join our team on a Substantive/Permanentbasis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With our largest service provision being Endoscopy,this is an exciting opportunity for anyonelooking to use their considerable endoscopy experience in a more leadership-focused rolewhilst alsocontinuingto support the NHS and its patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position will primarily be based out of the 18 Week Support HQ in Londonandoffers a 4-day per week working pattern. In addition, the Head Office team also have the resources and equipment to support Home Working when needed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your day will consist of providing management and leadership support to Endoscopy Nurses in Charge and the Endoscopy team, maintaining high standards of patient experience and care delivery,deputisingfor the 18 Week Support Chief Nurseand support in the development and implementation of strategic projects.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;18 Week Support is an RTT support provider which supports NHS Trusts with meeting their RTT pathways and 18-week waiting time targets. Like the NHS we work with, patient care is at the centre of everything we do, and our clinical teams are dedicated to ensuring excellent patient experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are an ethical and transparentorganisationthat is committed to the NHS and the delivery of high-quality care, and to helping NHS Trusts reduce RTT waiting times.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Post Summary&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Band 8c Head of Nursing – Endoscopy&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Substantive/Permanent Post&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Highly competitive annual salary&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;London (services span across the UK)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting to the 18 Week Support Chief Nurse&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full time (4-days per week)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Benefits include;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pension contribution&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Private health insurance&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;27 days’ Annual Leave + Bank Holidays&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Travel &amp; accommodation costs covered&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Induction, CPD and career opportunities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicant Requirements&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Registered Nurse/NMC PIN&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Master’s Degree (or working towards) or equivalent&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Minimum of 3 years’ experience at Band 8a level or above&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience working in partnership with MDT&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience in managing clinical governance, risk management, risk handling and complaints&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please see enclosed job description for full post details.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
